The number of confirmed Covid-19  cases on Saturday surged to 26,485, an increase representing a positivity rate of 27.3%, according to the National Institute for Communicable Diseases. Another 175 deaths were reported, bringing SA's overall death toll to 61,507. SA now has a total of 2,046,311 laboratory-confirmed cases. Gauteng still accounts for the majority of new cases (61%), followed by the Western Cape (11%), and Limpopo (7%). A staggering 16,091 cases were confirmed in Gauteng for Saturday, compared to 2,999 in the Western Cape and 1,780 in Limpopo. Another 557 people were admitted to hospital on Saturday. A total of 13,846 people are currently in hospital countrywide with Covid-19.